author: CNN
description:
Transportation Secretary Sean Duffy said Monday that an increased number of controllers have already called out sick during the federal government shutdown. To maintain safety with fewer controllers the Federal Aviation Administration will delay flights as needed.

“Our priorities are safety, and so if we have additional calls, we will reduce the flow consistent with a rate that’s safe for the American people,” Duffy said.

CNN aviation correspondent Pete Muntean reports. #CNN #News
title: DOT sees increase in air traffic controllers calling out sick

author: CNN
description: House Speaker Mike Johnson made clear that he’s counting on Senate Democrats to cave and back Republicans’ House-passed bill to reopen the government, as the shutdown drags into a second week and the House remains out of session for the third week in a row. CNN's Arlette Saenz reports. #CNN #News
title: House Speaker's surprising admission about government shutdown

author: CNN
description:
The Trump administration’s efforts to deploy National Guard troops to Democrat-led cities have prompted a legal showdown between the White House and state and local officials. Illinois and Chicago sued the administration, asking a federal court to halt the federalization of National Guard troops from that state and Texas, calling the move “patently unlawful.” On Sunday, a federal judge temporarily blocked the deployment of National Guard members to Portland, Oregon.

CNN's Manu Raju discusses with his "Inside Politics" panel: the AP's Seung Min Kim, the Atlanta Journal-Constitution's Tia Mitchell and Axios's Hans Nichols. #CNN #News
title: Legal battles erupt over White House's moves to deploy National Guard to Portland and Chicago

author: CNN
description: Police are investigating a house fire at a South Carolina district judge’s home. Three people were hospitalized, but the cause of the fire is currently unknown.
title: Investigation underway after fire at judge's home

Swedish activist Greta Thunberg and other Gaza aid flotilla participants arrived in Greece after being deported from Israel earlier today.

#cnn #news #gretathunberg #greece #sumudflotilla

author: CNN
description:
French Prime Minister Sebastien Lecornu resigned Monday just hours after he unveiled his new cabinet, in a shock move that plunged the country further into political crisis.

The prime minister – a key ally of embattled French President Emmanuel Macron – had not even been in office for four weeks, meaning he departs with the ignominious distinction of being the shortest-serving French prime minister since the Fifth Republic began.

Becky Anderson speaks with CNN senior international correspondent Melissa Bell. #CNN #News
title: France's Prime Minister resigns after less than a month on the job

author: CNN
description: French Prime Minister Sébastien Lecornu resigned after less than four weeks in office, making him President Emmanuel Macron's fifth prime minister in less than two years. CNN's Melissa Bell explains how this move may plunge the country further into political chaos. #cnn #news
title: France just lost another prime minister — what’s going on?

author: CNN
description: Video from what appears to be a Russian first person view attack drone flying down the streets of the Ukrainian city, Kramatorsk, could signal a huge problem for Ukrainian forces. CNN's Nick Paton Walsh reports. #cnn #news
title: Russians deploy new drone with fibre optic cable

author: CNN
description:
Adelita Grijalva decisively won a special election in Arizona's Second Congressional District two weeks ago, but she still hasn't been sworn into office. House Speaker Mike Johnson's office tells CNN that she will be sworn in when the House returns to session. 

CNN's Sara Sidner speaks with Congresswoman-Elect Adelita Grijalva (D-AZ). #CNN #News
title: Speaker Johnson yet to swear in newly elected Democratic lawmaker

author: CNN
description: For a second time, a Trump-appointed judge has blocked President Trump from sending troops into Portland. CNN's Alayna Treene reports. #cnn #portland #judge #trump #troops
title: Judge again blocks Trump from sending troops into Portland

author: CNN
description: Eighty years after the Japanese surrendered, formally ending World War II, CNN’s Stephanie Elam sat down with U.S. Navy veteran John DeLeo, who served on the USS Missouri during the war. DeLeo says he first boarded the Missouri in May of 1944 when he was 19 years old. He recalls what life was like on the “Mighty Mo,” witnessing the aftermath of a Kamakazi attack and watching as members of the Japanese Imperial Government boarded the Missouri on September 2, 1945, to take part in the surrender ceremony.  #CNN #News
title: WWII Navy veteran describes the moment when kamikaze plane hit USS Missouri

author: CNN
description:
A local artist in India portrayed President Donald Trump as the "demon" for the recent Durga Puja Festival. The organizers told CNN News 18, that the decision was not random and it was a response to Trump's 50 percent tariff on Indian goods.

#cnn #news #india #trump #durgapuja #durgapuja2025
title: Trump depicted as 'demon' at Indian festival

author: CNN
description:
The federal government shutdown enters its sixth day, with no signs yet of an end to the standoff.
Sara Sidner speaks with CNN correspondent Arlette Saenz, who reports from Capitol Hill, and John Berman speaks with Rep. Nicole Malliotakis (R-NY). #CNN #News
title: Day 6 of government shutdown with no end yet to impasse

author: CNN
description: Heavy monsoon rains caused landslides and flooding in Nepal, leaving at least 50 dead according to Reuters. The military was called in to evacuate villagers from areas at risk to safer locations. Monsoon season normally runs from June until September, killing hundreds each year.
title: Villagers evacuated by helicopter as floods hit Nepal

author: CNN
description:
Hamas, Israel and the US are set to start talks in Egypt today to work toward finalizing a deal based on President Trump’s Gaza ceasefire plan. Trump said he expects negotiations to take “a couple of days” and was told the first phase would be completed this week and urged negotiators to “MOVE FAST.” He earlier told CNN that Hamas faces “obliteration” if it refuses to cede power in Gaza.

Audie Cornish discusses with her "CNN This Morning" group chat: former deputy assistant Secretary of State in the Obama administration Joel Rubin, CNN senior media analyst Sara Fischer and CNN Politics senior reporter Stephen Collinson. #CNN #News
title: Trump shifts pressure to Israel after Hamas response

title: Hundreds of trekkers rescued from Mt Everest
